```java
class Solution {
    public int[] getOrder(int[][] tasks) {
        // intuition - sort tasks as enqueue time
        // then keep a waiting list as requirements -- here we use heap
        int n = tasks.length;
        int[][] memo = new int[n][3];

        // we could create an object for this purpose - track task index/id
        for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
            memo[i][0] = i;
            memo[i][1] = tasks[i][0];
            memo[i][2] = tasks[i][1];
        }

        // sort tasks
        Arrays.sort(memo, (m1, m2) -> m1[1] - m2[1]);
        // create the heap as we need
        PriorityQueue<int[]> pq = new PriorityQueue<>((m1, m2) -> 
            m1[2] != m2[2] ? m1[2] - m2[2] : m1[0] - m2[0]);

        int time = 0;
        // cur - current running task, itr - traverse task one by one
        int cur = 0, itr = 0;
        int[] res = new int[n];
        while (cur < n) {
            // if enquetime <= current time, means we could add into waiting list
            while (itr < n && memo[itr][1] <= time) {
                pq.offer(memo[itr]);
                itr++;
            }
            // if no waiting, we run it & update the time as its entry time
            if (pq.isEmpty()) {
                time = memo[itr][1];
                continue;
            }
            // find the next avaliable one from heap
            int[] next = pq.poll();
            // note down order
            res[cur] = next[0];
            // control time window
            time += next[2];
            cur++;
        }

        return res;
    }
}
```

```java
class Solution {
    public int minCharacters(String a, String b) {
        Map<Character, Integer> countA = new HashMap<>();
        Map<Character, Integer> countB = new HashMap<>();

        int m = a.length(), n = b.length();
        for (int i = 0; i < m; ++i) {
            countA.put(a.charAt(i), countA.getOrDefault(a.charAt(i), 0) + 1);
        }

        for (int j = 0; j < n; ++j) {
            countB.put(b.charAt(j), countB.getOrDefault(b.charAt(j), 0) + 1);
        }

        int res1 = Integer.MAX_VALUE;
        int res2 = Integer.MAX_VALUE;
        int res3 = Integer.MAX_VALUE;
        for (char c = 'a'; c <= 'z'; ++c) {
            res1 = Math.min(res1, Math.min(minChangeForLt(c, countA, countB), minChangeForLt(c, countB, countA)));
            res2 = Math.min(res2, countForEq(countA, c));
            res3 = Math.min(res3, countForEq(countB, c));
        }

        return Math.min(res1, res2 + res3);
    }

    private int minChangeForLt(char c, Map<Character, Integer> smaller, Map<Character, Integer> greaterEq) {
        int res = 0;

        if (c == 'a') {
            return Integer.MAX_VALUE;
        }

        for (var entry : smaller.entrySet()) {
            if (entry.getKey() >= c) {
                res += entry.getValue();
            }
        }

        for (var entry : greaterEq.entrySet()) {
            if (entry.getKey() < c) {
                res += entry.getValue();
            }
        }

        return res;
    }

    private int countForEq(Map<Character, Integer> count, char c) {
        int res = 0;

        for (var entry : count.entrySet()) {
            if (entry.getKey() != c) {
                res += entry.getValue();
            }
        }

        return res;
    }
}
```

Merge sort:

```java
class Solution {
    public int[] sortArray(int[] nums) {
        return sortHelper(nums, 0, nums.length - 1);
    }

    private int[] sortHelper(int[] nums, int start, int end) {
        if (start > end) {
            return new int[0];
        } else if (start == end) {
            return new int[] {nums[start]};
        }

        int mid = start + (end - start) / 2;
        int[] left = sortHelper(nums, start, mid);
        int[] right = sortHelper(nums, mid + 1, end);

        int m = left.length, n = right.length, i1 = 0, i2 = 0;
        int[] res = new int[m + n];
        for (int i = 0; i < res.length; ++i) {
            if (i1 >= m || i2 < n && left[i1] > right[i2]) {
