### 思路
Use two stacks, stack 1 saves elements in the order received and stack 2 is used for peek and pop (reverse order of the elements).
For push, add elements to stack 1
For pop, check if stack 2 is empty. If yes, move all elements from stack 1 to stack 2 (reversed order). Pop the last element of stack 2.
For peek. check if stack 2 is empty. If yes, move all elements from stack 1 to stack 2 (reversed order). Return the last element of stack 2.
For empty, check if both stack 1 and stack2 are empty.

